Detailed Description

Class Definition CGET_ROSPECS_RESPONSE for LLRP message GET_ROSPECS_RESPONSE.

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 10.1.14

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 16.1.16

This is the response by the Reader to a GET_ROSPECS command. If there are no ROSpecs configured at the Reader, the response is just the LLRPStatus parameter with the success code. Else, a list of ROSpec parameter is returned by the Reader, along with the success code in the LLRPStatus parameter.

void LLRP::CGET_ROSPECS_RESPONSE::assimilateSubParameters (  CErrorDetails *  pError  )  [virtual]
 

Assimilates the decoded sub-parameters into m_listAllSubParameters.

After fields are decoded, the CDecoder itself takes care of gathering the subparameters into m_listAllSubParameters. Once the end of the enclosing TLV (or message) is reached this assimilateSubParameters() function is called to create parameter refrences from the primary member variables.
